%20launched%20the%20India%20chapter%20about%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20firm's%20sixth%20location%20globally.%20Antler%20India%20has%20a%20%2475%20million%20fund%2C%20which%20we%20closed%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20plan%20is%20to%20invest%20in%20120%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-startups-get-bought-up-by-private-equity-vc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estartups%20%3C%2Fa%3Eover%20four%20years%2C%20and%20we%20have%20about%2065%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20classic%20Antler%20model%20includes%20running%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-vc-firms-funding-creator-economy-startups-next-phase-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecohort%20of%20individuals%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewho%20are%20transitioning%20from%20being%20employees%20to%20startup%20founders.%20We%20help%20them%20look%20for%20their%20cofounders%20and%20give%20shape%20to%20their%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20we%20do%20differently%20in%20India%20is%20we%20run%20a%20cohort%20for%20teams%20as%20well.%20We%20found%20that%20there%20is%20a%20social%20tendency%20for%20people%20to%20prefer%20going%20into%20business%20with%20people%20they%20have%20known%20from%20college%20or%20work%2C%20and%20we%20welcome%20founders%20who%20may%20already%20have%20a%20team%20or%20product%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20team%20and%20I%20receive%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-apply-y-combinator-application-down-market-successful-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4%2C000%20to%205%2C000%20applications%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we%20select%20100%20people%20to%20join%20our%20individual%20founders'%20cohort.%20The%20program%20runs%20for%20six%20months%2C%20and%20we%20end%20up%20investing%20in%2020-25%20people%2C%20or%20eight%20to%2010%20companies.%20We%20give%20them%20a%20sum%20of%20%24250%2C000%20to%20fund%20their%20idea%2C%20and%20another%20%24250%2C000%20once%20they%20raise%20additional%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20a%20founder%20myself%20and%20have%20run%20a%20company%20in%20the%202010s.%20I%20have%20seen%20two%20main%20positive%20shifts%20in%20the%20Indian%20startup%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20attract%20talent%20than%20it%20was%2010%20years%20ago.%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20entitlement%20and%20questioning%20from%20potential%20employees%2C%20because%20working%20for%20startups%20instead%20of%20long-established%20companies%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20risk.%20Since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20shift%2C%20and%20people%20are%20keen%20to%20join%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounders%20are%20getting%20more%20mature%20by%20the%20year%20and%20have%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20what%20it%20takes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20more%20frugal%20because%20they%20know%20capital%20is%20tight%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20they%20have%20given%20their%20industry%20more%20thought.%20They're%20not%20getting%20into%20business%20because%20something%20is%20hot%20and%20are%20instead%20building%20for%20the%20next%20five%20to%2010%20years.%20They%20also%20assume%20that%20their%20products%20will%20need%20higher%20traction%20to%20raise%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20would%20have%20been%20invested%20in%20them%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20things%20I%20look%20for%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsequoia-partner-jess-lee-advice-for-startup-founders-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst-time%20founders%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a01f9b1-7907-4c47-aa10-ead284c40a4d%5C%22%3EFive%20founder%20traits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExecution%20and%20strategy%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20is%20their%20ability%20to%20iterate%20fast%20%E2%80%94%20move%20between%20ideas%2C%20drop%20things%2C%20and%20find%20something%20new%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20seek%20people%20who%20have%20ideas%20that%20match%20their%20skill%20sets.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20invest%20in%20an%20AI%20company%20where%20none%20of%20the%20founders%20have%20solid%20tech%20expertise.%20In%20the%20early%20or%20%26quot%3Bzero%20to%20one%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bone%20to%2010%26quot%3B%20stages%2C%20founders%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20things%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrit%20and%20tenacity%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEither%20in%20their%20personal%20life%20or%20professional%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECustomer%20obsession%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20spend%20the%20longest%20time%20gauging%20how%20obsessed%20a%20founder%20is%20with%20their%20customer%20and%20problem%20statement.%20We%20want%20to%20know%20if%20it's%20just%20a%20flash%20in%20the%20pan%20or%20if%20it's%20something%20they%20have%20been%20debating%20over%20many%20years.%20Does%20the%20founder%20really%20feel%20the%20pain%20of%20the%20customer%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20people%20who%20are%20not%20just%20armchair%20experts%20but%20have%20worked%20with%20customers%20and%20gotten%20their%20hands%20dirty.%20Someone%20who%20has%20spent%20their%20professional%20life%20making%20presentations%20and%20in%20conference%20rooms%20may%20not%20cut%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommunication%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Another%20thing%20we%20look%20for%20is%20a%20high%20level%20of%20clarity%20in%20thinking%20and%20how%20they%20communicate.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20venture%20capital%20is%20a%20continuous%20fundraising%20game%20%E2%80%94%20you%20have%20to%20always%20keep%20finding%20good%20talent%2C%20as%20well%20as%20keep%20telling%20new%20investors%20and%20the%20media%20your%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20try%20to%20gauge%20if%20the%20person%20is%20getting%20mixed%20up%2C%20or%20if%20they're%20clear%20about%20what%20they're%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmbition%20and%20scale%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20venture%20capital%20industry%20does%20not%20work%20if%20you%20want%20small%20outcomes.%20Even%20if%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eyou%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20unicorn%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20is%20valued%20at%20%241%20billion%2C%20you%20still%20need%20to%20think%20in%20terms%20of%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20of%20valuation%20and%20foresee%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20using%20your%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22019aa888-dfdf-4ac4-bda4-422664c1e934%5C%22%3EPlus%20an%20X-factor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20look%20for%20people%20who%20score%20about%2080%25%20to%20100%25%20on%20each%20of%20these%20criteria.%20Instead%2C%20we%20prefer%20if%2C%20for%20one%20to%20two%20of%20the%20five%20traits%2C%20they%20demonstrate%20a%20spike%20or%20an%20X%20factor%20%E2%80%94%20they%20immediately%20stand%20out%20as%20someone%20who%20is%20world%3Cstrong%3E-%3C%2Fstrong%3Eclass%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20execution%20or%20communication%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20people%20who%20are%20terrible%20at%20some%20things%20but%20exceptional%20at%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8cf18ff-f29f-4d97-9753-7fe9d1705a42%5C%22%3ECofounder%20compl%3Cstrong%3Ee%3C%2Fstrong%3Ements%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20our%20participants%20look%20for%20their%20cofounders%20after%20they've%20entered%20the%20cohort%2C%20and%20we%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20attention%20matching%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20experience%2C%20India%20is%20not%20a%20country%20where%20teaching%20communication%20is%20emphasized%20a%20lot%2C%20so%20we%20ask%20each%20participant%2060%20questions%20to%20understand%20their%20values%2C%20working%20styles%2C%20and%20personality%20types.%20We%20look%20for%20complements%20and%20see%20pair-ups%20between%20one%20person%20with%20a%20technical%20background%20and%20one%20person%20with%20business%20acumen.%20If%20a%20third%20cofounder%20is%20needed%2C%20they%20usually%20come%20with%20operations%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20company%20we%20recently%20funded%20is%20working%20on%20lis